description:
IPC handlers use inconsistent patterns for accessing engines.

Pattern A - Direct vault access (read-only):
```typescript
ipcMain.handle('notes:list', async () => {
  const vault = requireVault(deps);
  return vault.list();
});
```

Pattern B - Using withEngines helper (write operations):
```typescript
ipcMain.handle('notes:save', withEngines(deps, async (engines, note) => {...}));
```

The EngineOrchestrator (apps/desktop/electron/main/src/EngineOrchestrator.ts) exists but isn't used consistently in all handlers.

Solution:
1. Document the intentional difference between patterns in code comments
2. Refactor write operations to use EngineOrchestrator consistently
3. Add CONTRIBUTING.md documentation for when to use each pattern

Files: apps/desktop/electron/main/src/handlers/notesHandlers.ts, apps/desktop/electron/main/src/EngineOrchestrator.ts

Consolidate wrapError function into shared handler utilities.

Identical wrapError function duplicated in two handler files:

**notesHandlers.ts (lines 52-59):**
```typescript
function wrapError(error: unknown): never {
  if (error instanceof ScribeError) {
    const userError = new Error(error.getUserMessage());
    userError.name = error.code;
    throw userError;
  }
  throw error;
}
```

**peopleHandlers.ts (lines 43-50):** Identical implementation

**Implementation Steps:**
