# [Phase 0.1] Verify SyncEngine is not initialized unless explicitly enabled

## Problem Statement
Sync MUST be disabled by default to protect enterprise/corporate users with data governance requirements. This task ensures no sync-related code runs unless the user explicitly enables sync.

## Why This is Critical (P0)
- **Corporate/enterprise environments** have data governance policies prohibiting external sync
- **Regulated industries** (healthcare, finance, legal) have strict data residency requirements
- **Privacy-conscious users** want all data to remain local
- **Zero network calls when disabled** - no sync-related network traffic whatsoever

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Check sync config before initialization
```typescript
// apps/desktop/electron/main/src/main.ts

async function initializeEngines(vaultPath: string): Promise<void> {
  // ... existing engine initialization ...

  // ONLY initialize sync engine if explicitly enabled in vault config
  const syncConfig = await loadSyncConfig(vaultPath);
  if (syncConfig?.enabled === true) {
    deps.syncEngine = await createSyncEngine({
      vaultPath,
      serverUrl: syncConfig.serverUrl,
      // ... other config
    });
  } else {
    // Explicitly set to null - sync is disabled
    deps.syncEngine = null;
    logger.info('Sync disabled - no sync engine initialized');
  }
}
```

### 2. Add sync config loading helper
```typescript
// packages/engine-sync/src/sync-config.ts

interface SyncConfig {
  enabled: boolean;
  serverUrl: string;
  apiKeyHash: string;
  deviceId: string;
  lastSyncSequence: number;
  enabledAt: number;
}

export async function loadSyncConfig(vaultPath: string): Promise<SyncConfig | null> {
  const configPath = path.join(vaultPath, '.scribe', 'sync.json');
  try {
    const content = await fs.readFile(configPath, 'utf-8');
    return JSON.parse(content) as SyncConfig;
  } catch {
    return null; // Config doesn't exist = sync never enabled
  }
}
```

### 3. Update HandlerDependencies
Ensure syncEngine is nullable and handlers check before using:
```typescript
// apps/desktop/electron/main/src/handlers/types.ts
export interface HandlerDependencies {
  // ... existing deps ...
  syncEngine: SyncEngine | null;  // Explicitly nullable
}
```

