# [Phase 0.2] Verify no network calls occur when sync is disabled

## Problem Statement
When sync is disabled, there must be ZERO network traffic related to sync. This is not just about skipping sync operations - it's about ensuring no telemetry, no health checks, no anything that phones home.

## Why This is Critical (P0)
- Enterprise security teams audit network traffic
- Some corporate environments block unknown endpoints
- Users should have full confidence that "disabled" means "disabled"
- GDPR and other regulations may require this guarantee

## Implementation Approach

### 1. Conditional import of sync transport
```typescript
// packages/engine-sync/src/sync-engine.ts

export class SyncEngine {
  private transport: SyncTransport | null = null;

  constructor(config: SyncEngineConfig) {
    if (!config.enabled) {
      // Don't even create the transport - no HTTP client instantiated
      this.transport = null;
      return;
    }
    this.transport = new SyncTransport(config.serverUrl);
  }
}
```

### 2. Guard all network operations
```typescript
// Every method that might make network calls:
async triggerSync(): Promise<SyncResult> {
  if (!this.transport) {
    return { pushed: 0, pulled: 0, conflicts: 0, errors: ['Sync disabled'] };
  }
  // ... actual sync logic
}
```

### 3. NetworkMonitor should not ping when disabled
```typescript
// packages/engine-sync/src/network-monitor.ts

export class NetworkMonitor {
  constructor(private enabled: boolean) {
    if (!enabled) {
      // Don't set up any listeners or polling
      return;
    }
    // Set up Electron net listeners only if enabled
    net.on('online', () => this.setOnline(true));
    net.on('offline', () => this.setOnline(false));
  }
}
```

