# Implement Version Display and Update Checking UI

## What
Build the version and update checking section in GeneralSettings, showing current version and providing update management.

## Why
- **User Visibility**: Users should know what version they're running
- **Update Management**: Centralized place for checking and installing updates
- **Leverages Existing Hook**: useUpdateStatus already tracks all update states

## Technical Approach

### Component Implementation
```tsx
// VersionSetting.tsx
import { Button, Text } from '@scribe/design-system';
import { useUpdateStatus } from '../../../hooks/useUpdateStatus';

export function VersionSetting() {
  const { status, version, error, installUpdate } = useUpdateStatus();

  const checkForUpdates = () => {
    window.scribe.update.check();
  };

  return (
    <div className={styles.versionSetting}>
      <Text variant="body">v{__APP_VERSION__}</Text>

      <div className={styles.updateControls}>
        {renderUpdateButton()}
        {renderStatusMessage()}
      </div>
    </div>
  );

  function renderUpdateButton() {
    switch (status) {
      case 'idle':
        return <Button onClick={checkForUpdates}>Check for Updates</Button>;
      case 'checking':
        return <Button disabled>Checking...</Button>;
      case 'downloading':
        return <Button disabled>Downloading...</Button>;
      case 'ready':
        return <Button onClick={installUpdate}>Restart to Update</Button>;
      case 'error':
        return <Button onClick={checkForUpdates}>Retry Check</Button>;
    }
  }

  function renderStatusMessage() {
    switch (status) {
      case 'ready':
        return <Text variant="body" color="success">Update ready: v{version}</Text>;
      case 'error':
        return <Text variant="body" color="danger">{error}</Text>;
      default:
        return null;
    }
  }
}
```

### State Machine (from useUpdateStatus)
```
idle -> checking -> downloading -> ready
  |        |            |           |
  v        v            v           v
error   (idle)       (idle)     (restart)
```

### Update Flow
1. **Idle**: Show "Check for Updates" button
2. **Checking**: Show "Checking..." (disabled)
3. **Downloading**: Show "Downloading..." (disabled)
4. **Ready**: Show "Restart to Update" (enabled, calls installUpdate)
5. **Error**: Show error message, "Retry Check" button

### After "No Update Available"
The useUpdateStatus hook returns to 'idle' when no update is found. We could enhance to show a brief "You're up to date" message:
```tsx
const [lastCheckResult, setLastCheckResult] = useState<'none' | 'up-to-date' | null>(null);

