# Implement Vault Switching UI with Validation

## What
Enable the "Change" button in vault settings, allowing users to select and switch to a different vault folder. Uses the restart-based approach (not hot-reload).

## Why
- **Primary Vault Management Feature**: Users need to switch between vaults
- **Validation Feedback**: Clear errors when selected folder isn't a valid vault
- **Complete User Flow**: From folder selection to restart prompt

## Technical Approach

### UI Flow (Restart-Based)
1. User clicks "Change" button
2. Native folder picker opens (via dialog:selectFolder)
3. User selects a folder
4. System validates the folder is a valid vault
5. If invalid: Show inline error message
6. If valid: Save to config, show restart dialog
7. User clicks "Restart Now" or "Later"

### Component Implementation
```tsx
function VaultLocationSetting() {
  const [currentPath, setCurrentPath] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [validationError, setValidationError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [showRestartDialog, setShowRestartDialog] = useState(false);

  // Load current vault path on mount
  useEffect(() => {
    window.scribe.vault.getPath().then(setCurrentPath);
  }, []);

  const handleChangeVault = async () => {
    setValidationError(null);

    // 1. Open folder picker
    const selectedPath = await window.scribe.dialog.selectFolder({
      title: 'Select Scribe Vault',
      defaultPath: currentPath || undefined,
    });

    if (!selectedPath) return; // User cancelled

    // 2. Validate and set path (handler does validation)
    const result = await window.scribe.vault.setPath(selectedPath);

    if (!result.success) {
      setValidationError(result.error || 'Failed to switch vault');
      return;
    }

    // 3. Show restart dialog
    if (result.requiresRestart) {
      setShowRestartDialog(true);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <Text variant="code">{currentPath}</Text>
      {validationError && <Text color="danger">{validationError}</Text>}
      <Button onClick={handleChangeVault}>Change</Button>

      {showRestartDialog && (
        <RestartDialog 
          onRestartNow={() => window.scribe.app.relaunch()}
          onLater={() => setShowRestartDialog(false)}
        />
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Restart Dialog
