# Create useSettingsPage Hook for State Management

## What
Create a custom hook to manage Settings page state: open/close, active section, and any transient settings state.

## Why
- **Centralized State**: Keep settings-related state in one place
- **Reusability**: Can be used from App.tsx and passed down
- **Separation of Concerns**: UI logic separate from component rendering
- **Future Expansion**: Easy to add more state (unsaved changes warning, etc.)

## Technical Approach

### Hook API
```typescript
// useSettingsPage.ts
export type SettingsSection = 'general' | 'changelog';

export interface UseSettingsPageReturn {
  // Modal state
  isOpen: boolean;
  open: () => void;
  close: () => void;
  toggle: () => void;

  // Section navigation
  activeSection: SettingsSection;
  setActiveSection: (section: SettingsSection) => void;
}

export function useSettingsPage(): UseSettingsPageReturn {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
  const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useState<SettingsSection>('general');

  const open = useCallback(() => {
    setIsOpen(true);
    setActiveSection('general'); // Reset to default on open
  }, []);

  const close = useCallback(() => {
    setIsOpen(false);
  }, []);

  const toggle = useCallback(() => {
    setIsOpen(prev => !prev);
  }, []);

  return {
    isOpen,
    open,
    close,
    toggle,
    activeSection,
    setActiveSection,
  };
}
```

### Usage in App.tsx
```tsx
function App() {
  const settings = useSettingsPage();

  return (
    <div className={styles.app}>
      <Sidebar 
        onOpenSettings={settings.open}
        // ... other props
      />

      <SettingsPage 
        isOpen={settings.isOpen}
        onClose={settings.close}
        activeSection={settings.activeSection}
        onSelectSection={settings.setActiveSection}
      />

      {/* ... rest of app */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Future Extensions
This hook can be extended to support:
- **Dirty state tracking**: Warn before closing with unsaved changes
- **Keyboard shortcuts**: Cmd+, to open settings
- **Deep linking**: Open to specific section (e.g., from toast "Update Settings")
- **History**: Remember last visited section

### Potential Addition: Keyboard Shortcut
```typescript
// Inside the hook
useEffect(() => {
  const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    // Cmd+, (macOS) or Ctrl+, (Windows/Linux) opens settings
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === ',') {
      e.preventDefault();
      toggle();
    }
  };

  window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
}, [toggle]);
```

